\let\x{\mi{x}}
\let\y{\mi{y}}

\p{Let \math{\x} and \math{\y} be integers such that \math{\equals{\plus{\x}{\y}}{\mn{0}}}.}]]></html:pre>
                <html:p>It is annoying that we have to always wrap things in <html:code><![CDATA[\math]]></html:code>. By combining first-class functions, lazy arguments, and fluid bindings, we can lift this requirement:</html:p>
