            <fr:addr>forest://forester/jms-00RL</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RL.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support › emitting XML and resolving namespaces › a worked example"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RJ.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support › emitting XML and resolving namespaces" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RJ" type="local"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RH.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RH" type="local"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RF.xml" title="Forester 4.0" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RF" type="local">Forester 4.0</fr:link> › enhanced XML support</fr:link> › emitting XML and resolving namespaces</fr:link> › a worked example</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>The following code causes MathML to be emitted (in the correct namespace), combining <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RK.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support › emitting XML and resolving namespaces › XML namespace declaration" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RK" type="local">Feature <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-00RK" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RM.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support › emitting XML and resolving namespaces › XML literals" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RM" type="local">Feature <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-00RM" /></fr:link>:</html:p>
            <html:pre><![CDATA[\xmlns:mml{http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML}
\<mml:math>[display]{block}{
 \<mml:mrow>{
  \<mml:msup>{
   \<mml:mi>{x}
   \<mml:mn>{2}
  }
  \<mml:mo>{+}
  \<mml:mi>{x}
 }
}]]></html:pre>
            <html:p>The above displays as follows:</html:p>
            <mml:math display="block" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <mml:mrow xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
     <mml:msup xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
      <mml:mi xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">x</mml:mi>
      <mml:mn xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">2</mml:mn>
     </mml:msup>
     <mml:mo xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">+</mml:mo>
     <mml:mi xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">x</mml:mi>
    </mml:mrow>
   </mml:math>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
